Relative molecular mass , Mr           Mr of a substance is defined as 'average mass' of the molecule of an element or compound compared with 1 twelveth the mass of a C-12 atom.         To obtain  relative molecular mass  or   formula masses,  we add together the individual relative atomic masses of the atoms present in the molecule in question.         Example:         Sulphuric Acid H 2 SO 4                    Ar           Qty              Total    H        1              2                     2    S       32             1                    32    O      16             4                     64                                                                     98